Tyco International Management Company ("Tyco") is certifying Safe Harbor for personal information relating to (1) Employee/Employment Data; (2) Corporate Compliance and Training Programs Data; and (3) Customer Relationship Management Data as set out below:

(1) 	Employee/Employment Data. Tyco processes employee/employment personal data to comply with its legal obligations and to carry out and manage its: 
(A)	Human Resources Administration:  to provide the employment services necessary to manage, evaluate and compensate current, past or prospective employees and adhere to applicable employment laws;
(B)	Business Process Administration: to facilitate the efficient day-to-day running of business operations;
(C)	Safety and Security: to ensure the safety and protection of employees, resources, and communities;
(D)	Ethics and Compliance Programs: to manage compliance with Tyco’s Guide to Ethical Conduct, corporate policies and programs and applicable laws; and 
(E)	Internal Audit: to manage compliance with Tyco’s internal audit programs and applicable laws. 
Processing of this data will be conducted in accordance with applicable law and within such purpose limitations notified to the employees in the Global Employee Privacy Notification.  

(2) Corporate Compliance and Training Program Data. Tyco also processes customer/vendor/business partner personal data as part of its global corporate compliance and training programs. These include:  
(A)	Tyco’s Third Party Management Program, which is implemented in accordance with Tyco’s anti-bribery/anti-corruption policy to enable Tyco to comply with global anti-bribery laws;
(B)	The Tyco Ombudsman concerns reporting and management systems;
(C)	Restricted Party Screening for compliance with global trade regulations or other laws; and
(D)	The Learning Management System for employee and third party training on products, services, and compliance.
Processing of this data will be conducted in accordance with applicable law and within such purpose limitations notified to the customers/vendors/business partners in the Tyco Global Privacy Statement.   
(3) Customer and employee data for customer relationship management and administration. Tyco also processes customer and employee data for the efficient operation and management of customer and business relationships, including the Global Sales Force Database.  
Processing of this data will be conducted in accordance with applicable law and within such purpose limitations notified to the customers/vendors/business partners in the Tyco Global Privacy Statement.
